/*
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  WiFiGuard — Phase 5                                                         ║
║  Risk scoring v2 + explainability + channel congestion + NEW marker         ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║  Changes from Phase 4:                                                       ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-1] RiskFactor struct { char label[24]; int8_t delta; }                  ║
║         Up to 5 factors per network stored in riskCache[].                   ║
║         computeRisk() fills both the score and the factors array.            ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-2] RiskCache array  riskCache[25]                                       ║
║         Populated after every scan, before showList().                       ║
║         Invalidated (score = -1) when portalRes changes so ANALYZE           ║
║         recomputes on next open.                                              ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-3] Channel congestion                                                   ║
║         channelCounts[14] computed once over all nets after scan.            ║
║         Overlapping channel detection: channels 1–13 consider ±4 neighbours ║
║         for interference (simplified model).                                 ║
║         Adds 0–10 pts to risk score with label "Channel congested".          ║
║         channelCounts[] must be built BEFORE computeRisk() is called.       ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-4] Score calibration                                                    ║
║         OPEN base = 60; WEP = 45; WPA = 22; WPA2 = 8; WPA3 = 3; else = 12  ║
║         Portal penalty: +15 (portal likely), +8 (no internet),              ║
║           +5 (connect fail), −5 (no portal)                                  ║
║         SSID keyword bonus: free+10, guest+5, airport+5, hotel+5,           ║
║           public+5, cafe+3, starbucks+5                                      ║
║         Signal penalty: <−85 = +12, <−75 = +8, <−65 = +4                   ║
║         Channel congestion: +2 per overlapping AP (max +10)                 ║
║         Hard cap: max 100.  OPEN alone never exceeds 75 (portal pushes to   ║
║         90). WPA3 with no portal floors at 3.                               ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-5] ANALYZE screen "Why?" section                                        ║
║         Shows top 3 RiskFactors as bullet rows below the data rows.         ║
║         Format: "• label  +N" (delta in colour matching sign).              ║
║         Only drawn if factorCount > 0.                                       ║
║         Uses cached riskCache[sel] — no recompute on every draw.            ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-6] "NEW" marker                                                         ║
║         prevBSSIDs[25] stores packed uint64_t of each BSSID from the        ║
║         previous scan (zeroed on first run).                                 ║
║         isNew[25] bool array set after each scan by comparing BSSIDs.       ║
║         LIST panel: draws "NEW" tag in magenta on the right of the row       ║
║         when isNew[idx] is true (replaces sec tag for that row).             ║
║         isNew cleared on each full scan.                                     ║
║                                                                              ║
║  [P5-7] riskScore() / riskScoreWithPortal() now delegate to cache.          ║
║         Old inline functions removed; computeRisk() is the single source.   ║
║                                                                              ║
║  All Phase 1–4 features preserved without regression.                       ║
║  Pins: BAT_ADC=34, TFT_BL=4, BTN_NEXT(L)=0, BTN_ACT(R)=35                 ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
*/

